## Feeding

**Omnivores** with a stronger herbivorous tendency than pure carnivores.

**Staple foods:**
- Quality omnivore flakes or micro-pellets
- Spirulina-enriched foods — Support the herbivorous component
- Blanched zucchini, spinach, peas (shelled) — Accepted and nutritionally useful

**Protein supplementation:**
- Frozen bloodworm — 2–3x per week
- Frozen brine shrimp — Good variety
- Daphnia — Digestive health benefit

**Live foods for breeding:**
- **Baby Brine Shrimp** — Conditioning food for breeding females. **[From Blackwater Aquatics](https://blackwateraquatics.ca/collections/live-foods).**
- **Daphnia** — Also excellent for fry from day 3. **[From Blackwater Aquatics](https://blackwateraquatics.ca/collections/live-foods).**
- **Microworms** — Ideal fry first food. **[From Blackwater Aquatics](https://blackwateraquatics.ca/collections/live-foods).**

