## Health

**White Spot (Ich):** Common in temperature-unstable or poorly conditioned tanks. Treat with heat (30°C for 2 weeks, ensure aeration) or half-dose medication.

**Fin Rot:** Bacterial. Improve water quality. Mild antibacterial treatment if persisting.

**Shimmying:** A wobbling, shaking movement without forward progress. Classically associated with low temperatures or poor water quality in hard-water livebearers. Improve conditions; often self-resolves once parameters are corrected.

**Internal worms:** Stringy faeces, weight loss despite eating. Treat with Levamisole.

